# Changelog

## 0.1.20 - 2026-06-02

- Added a deployment-level `Server Base URL` setting so each school can define its own host or IP once and let the Google OAuth callback URI populate from that value.
- Updated the Google setup flow to derive the callback hint from the configured server URL instead of relying on a hardcoded or manually guessed address.

## 0.1.19 - 2026-06-02

- Rewrote the Google page setup instructions to explicitly walk admins through Google Cloud Console, including exactly where to create the OAuth client and where to copy the Client ID and Client Secret from.
- Added clearer field-to-field mapping on the Google page so the OAuth configuration can be completed without leaving administrators guessing what belongs in each AthletiSync field.

## 0.1.18 - 2026-06-02

- Clarified the Google page setup copy so admins can see that the page is where they add the Google account connection AthletiSync will use for calendar access.
- Added callback URI guidance explaining that an internal IP address is acceptable when the browser reaches AthletiSync on the same network.

## 0.1.17 - 2026-06-02

- Moved Google OAuth client configuration off the general Settings page and back onto the Google page so the full Google setup flow lives in one place.
- Removed the legacy service-account setup path from the Google UI and kept the page focused on the dedicated Google account OAuth flow.

## 0.1.16 - 2026-06-02

- Added Google OAuth user-auth support for calendar sync, so districts can connect the dedicated Google calendar manager account instead of relying only on service-account JSON keys.
- Moved Google OAuth client configuration into the AthletiSync settings UI, with environment-variable fallback still supported for server-managed deployments.
- Reworked the Google page into a clearer two-step flow: connect an auth profile first, then save a calendar destination and test that specific calendar's access.

## 0.1.15 - 2026-04-11

- Hardened MSHSAA event identity to prefer stable public event references like `comp` and `tournament` when available.
- Updated sync event normalization so Google Calendar updates reuse stable MSHSAA matchup and tournament references instead of depending on mutable fields like title, opponent, or start time.
- Added coverage proving that rescheduled events with the same MSHSAA event reference keep the same internal source key.

## 0.1.14 - 2026-04-11

- Removed `Sports & Levels` and `Mappings` from the main navigation so the primary admin flow stays centered on MSHSAA source review.
- Moved mapping creation into the schedule preview panel on the MSHSAA source review page, including Google Calendar selection and optional level selection from the discovered schedule.
- Updated mapping saves to auto-create the underlying sport and level records when needed, so admins no longer need to manage those catalog pages directly.

## 0.1.13 - 2026-04-11

- Added sport-specific event formatter overrides so title and description patterns can be configured once per sport instead of per school year.
- Expanded formatter previews to show standard matchup, tournament, and multi-team examples using the same placeholder system as live Google event sync.
- Improved sync payload formatting so templates can use both a primary opponent and the full participant list for sports like golf, wrestling, and tournaments.

## 0.1.12 - 2026-04-11

- Added explicit school-year selection on the MSHSAA source review page so schedule previews can load future-year events directly instead of defaulting to the currently selected source year.

## 0.1.11 - 2026-04-11

- Fixed school-year discovery by probing MSHSAA activity schedule pages when the generic school schedule page exposes an empty year selector.
- Updated live sync year selection so future years exposed by MSHSAA activity pages can be discovered and used.

## 0.1.10 - 2026-04-11

- Made the left navigation sidebar sticky so the menu remains visible while scrolling long pages.

## 0.1.9 - 2026-04-11

- Moved the sidebar version label to a consistently visible position near the top of the menu so it remains visible on long pages like MSHSAA Source Review.

## 0.1.8 - 2026-04-11

- Added selected-activity highlighting and a scrollable activities pane on the MSHSAA source review page.
- Ordered activities by school-year flow using MSHSAA season metadata so fall items surface before winter and spring items.

## 0.1.7 - 2026-04-11

- Cleaned up the source review activity list so action buttons align in a consistent column with clearer row separation.
- Normalized schedule preview type labels so tournament-related rows display cleaner human-readable values instead of raw class strings.

## 0.1.6 - 2026-04-11

- Added the running AthletiSync version number to the sidebar so admins can confirm which build is active in the UI.

## 0.1.5 - 2026-04-11

- Moved MSHSAA source review into a dedicated two-pane page so activity discovery and schedule inspection no longer compete on the main Schools page.
- Replaced the inline `Preview Source` workflow with a cleaner `Review Source` navigation pattern.

## 0.1.4 - 2026-04-11

- Added a read-only in-app MSHSAA schedule browser so admins can inspect activities and their schedule rows before full sync setup.
- Extended the MSHSAA parser to extract level-of-play labels and normalized schedule rows from the live schedule page.

## 0.1.3 - 2026-04-11

- Simplified the school setup UI by removing the unused `External ID` field from the admin form.
- Added documentation for how administrators should locate and copy the correct MSHSAA school URL.

## 0.1.2 - 2026-04-11

- Added MSHSAA onboarding documentation and linked it from the main project docs.
- Added admin-side MSHSAA source validation on the Schools page so configured school URLs can be tested and previewed before sync setup.
- Refactored the MSHSAA parser to separate HTML parsing from HTTP fetches and added parser coverage tests.

## 0.1.1 - 2026-04-11

- Improved first-run admin flow with dedicated school year management and clearer dashboard summaries.
- Hardened mapping, dashboard, and sync routes to load related records cleanly and expose more useful state in the UI.
- Added integration-style application tests for login, health, dashboard access control, and settings updates.

## 0.1.0 - 2026-04-11

- Initial AthletiSync MVP scaffold.
- Added FastAPI application with session authentication, CSRF helpers, admin UI, and HTMX-ready templates.
- Added SQLAlchemy models, Alembic migration bootstrap, APScheduler integration, sync engine abstractions, and initial MSHSAA/Google Calendar service layers.
- Added Docker, Compose, environment example, documentation, and pytest coverage for core sync behavior.
